lt;Betrayal&gt;</span><hr size=1> With this storm brewing, endless battle, and strange events, it had been hard to find time alone. Vladire, laying on her stomach beside Malelick under the beautiful dead trees of Nektulos, realized how much she had missed her home in the past weeks. <br>
<br>
 Scattering leaves on the ground with idle hands she looked to Maleick and asked if he was hungry.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, it's getting late in the day. Should i send for something?&quot;<br>
<br>
 &quot;No, I'll go myself. It's beautiful weather for a short walk.&quot;<br>
<br>
She headed through the trees leaving Maleick dozing peacefully beside a log. Inside the halls of Neriak she was greeted warmly, meeting with old aquaintences along the way. At the entrance to her quarters she was approached by a formed element, almost standing guard. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hello, Vladire&quot;, an airy voice says.<br>
<br>
Instinctivly her hand moves to her weapon and she is surrounded by and air of tension. Jaw set, eyes locked. The element chuckles and states, &quot;So defensive you appear. Be calm, I am nothing to fear.&quot;<br>
 <br>
 With a small swirl of mist the element dissapears and Mythral stands before her. With the confusion of the last few days surrounding the Enchanter she does not let down her guard, but feels mostly at ease.<br>
<br>
&quot;And how are you this eve?&quot; He takes her hand and kisses it.<br>
<br>
Out of fear of the rumors (and embarrasment) she jerks her hand away.<br>
<br>
&quot;Quite well actually. I am gathering dinner for Maleick and I. He awaits me just outside.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh, may I join you? I have just prepared a stein of absinthe and I've no one to share it with.&quot;<br>
<br>
 His eyes bore into her. As if imploring to accept. They are beautiful and seem to change color if gazed at long enough. He is smiling. Absentmindedly she replies, &quot;Yes, please do.&quot;<br>
<br>
A strange feeling is encompassing her, almost as if she were being controlled. &quot;That is foolish&quot;, she reminds herself. <br>
<br>
They walk along quietly through the beautiful trees. Apon arriving back at the log they find Maleick awake and instructing young Teir'Dal Warriors, teaching them methods of destruction. <br>
<br>
&quot;We have company Maleick. Mythral just happened to be near the quarters.&quot; the fear and nervousness from before had nearly subsided.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh welcome Mythral, let us break bread and share a meal with you. It has been a while since we last met.&quot;<br>
<br>
Vladire has prepared a delicious dinner of steak and fruit and Mythral begins to speak of his battles in the past weeks. He is a great storyteller and his body and emotions dance with a sort of magical jubilance. His words are filled with rhymes and puns and jokes that errupt into laughter at times. The young couple listen intently with smiles on their faces before they realize that Mythral has refilled their pints of ale with absinthe 2 or 3 times over. Totally captivated by his words, they are led into the stories, into strange places, they see beautiful sunsets and the bloodiest of battle. And it all seems normal. As if it were order of the day the three are dancing and laughing like family. Mythral brings an end to his great tales and they sit, leaning comfortably against the log. Maleick releases a sigh of content and Mythral gives him sort of a half smile that emits the message 'rest'. After a short time Maleick is dozing again and Vladire is not far from it. Silently Mythral calls Vladires attention with his gaze.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come to me&quot;, he says.<br>
<br>
In a trusting manner she moves closer to Mythral and he places his hand to her throat. Her eyes are level with his. His thumb traces the contour of her neck. Sternly he says, &quot;You will enforce my will.&quot; and with those words he bites deeply into her neck. Vladire blinks confusedly and releases a small cry of pain, but it is gone before she can think further of it.<br>
<br>
The couple awake to daylight poking through the leaves in the forest. They exchange puzzled glances, as they cannot remeber last nights events, or why they would choose to sleep in the forest. Their bodies stiffened and sore from the ground, they stand, and stretch and begin to make their way out of the forrest and back to the rigorous work they had only been able to take a small break from.<br>
